# Go
*.test
*.out
/coverage.out
/cover.html
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# Local-dev Go workspace, generated on demand by `make workspace` when cli-guard
# is checked out side by side at ../cli-guard (ward#326). Never committed: a
# tracked `use (. ../cli-guard)` would break single-repo builds in CI and the
# warded headless clone, where the sibling is absent and `go build` would fail.
/go.work
/go.work.sum

# Build artifacts
/bin/
/dist/
/ward

# mkdocs build output
/site/

# Editor / OS
.DS_Store
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Local dev overrides
*.local

# Stray Python lockfile: ward ships no Python and denies bare `uv` (cmd/ward/hook.go).
# A uv.lock only ever lands here if a uv-using tool (e.g. pre-commit's Python hook
# envs) drops one in the tree. Never tracked - keep it invisible rather than churn.
uv.lock

# Runtime spec cache fetched by `make lock` / skew checks; never committed (ward#62).
# The committed spec lock is a distinct name (*.swagger.lock.json) and IS tracked.
*.swagger.v1.json
cmd/ward-kdl/main.go
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-read/main.go
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-write/main.go
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-admin/main.go

# A tiered area whose spec is a vendored local file (e.g. signoz) needs that spec
# read locally at lock time in each tier subdir, since the inheriting write/admin
# members resolve the same `spec` relative to their own dir. `make
# build-ward-kdl-tiers` copies the canonical cmd/ward-kdl/<spec> into each tier
# subdir before locking, so the copies are build-time inputs (like the generated
# main.go), never a source of truth - the committed spec is the base-dir one, and
# each tier's pruned *.openapi.lock.json IS tracked (ward#338).
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-read/*.openapi.json
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-write/*.openapi.json
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-admin/*.openapi.json

# specverb-gen emits one surface reference beside each Guardfile (the only path
# it knows); the reviewed copies live under docs/ward-kdl/ (ward#279). One per
# merged API (ward-kdl.<api>.guardfile.md), one per forgejo tier subdir (ward#240).
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl.*.guardfile.md
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-read/ward-kdl.*.guardfile.md
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-write/ward-kdl.*.guardfile.md
cmd/ward-kdl/ward-kdl-admin/ward-kdl.*.guardfile.md
